\label{def:reduced}
Given an $X,Y$-bipartite graph $G$ and partitions $\{U_0, U_1,\dots, U_k\}$ of $X$ and $\{V_0,
V_1,\dots, V_k\}$ of $Y$ satisfying conditions (i)-(v) of Lemma \ref{2colordegreeform}, we define the $(\ep, d)$-reduced graph of $G$ to be the bipartite graph $\Gamma$ on vertex set $\{U_1, \dots, U_k\} \cup \{V_1, \dots, V_k\}$ such that $U_iV_j$ is an edge of $\Gamma$ if $G'[U_i, V_j]$ has density at least $2d$.  For each $U_iV_j\in E(\Gamma)$, we assign red if $G'_R[U_i, V_j]$ has density at least $d$, and blue if $G'_B[U_i, V_j]$ has density at least $d$.

