Let $\epsilon > 0$.  Given a graph $G$ and two nonempty disjoint vertex sets $A, B \subset V$, we say that the pair $(A, B)$ is \emph{$\epsilon$-regular} if for every $X \subset A$ and $Y \subset B$ satisfying
\begin{equation*}
|X| > \epsilon |A| ~ ~ ~ \text{and} ~ ~ ~ |Y| > \epsilon |B|
\end{equation*}
we have
\begin{equation*}
|d(X, Y) - d(A, B)| < \epsilon.
\end{equation*}

