Let $X\subset V$ be  an irreducible  $k$-subvariety $X\subset V$ of codimension $L$ and $\bar X \subset \mP (V)$ 
be the corresponding projective variety. We define the {\it degree} $d(X)$  of $X$ as the number of $\bar k$-points in the intersection $\bar X\cap \mP (M)(\bar k)$ for generic subspaces $M$ of $V$ of dimension $L$ defined over over $\bar k$.

