Given a linear code $C\subseteq \mathbb{F}^{n}_{2}$, the \emph{dual code} $C^{\perp}$ is defined as,
 \begin{center}
   $C^{\perp}=\{ x \in \mathbb{F}^{n}_{2} | \langle x,c \rangle =0, \forall c \in C\}$  
 \end{center}
 where $\langle x, y\rangle$ is the standard inner product over $\mathbb{F}_{2}$.

