A \emph{matroid} $M$ is a pair $(E, \B)$ consisting of a finite set $E$ and a nonempty collection of subsets $\B=\B(M)$ of $E$, called the \emph{bases} of $M$, which satisfy the \emph{basis exchange axiom}: 
\begin{itemize}
\item If $B_1, B_2 \in \B$ and $b_1 \in B_1 - B_2$, then there exists $b_2 \in B_2 - B_1$ such that $(B_1 -  b_1) \cup b_2 \in \B$.
\end{itemize}

