A graph $G=(V,E)$ is a \emph{permutation graph} if and only if there is an ordering $v_1,v_2, \dotsc, v_n$ of the vertices of $V$ such that there is permutation $\tau$ of the numbers from $1$ to $n$ with the property that for all integers $1\leq i<j\leq n$
